    "Body": " Director, Sustainable Finance APAC Location: Singapore or Hong Kong Reporting to: Global Head of Sustainable Finance, S&P Global Ratings Key Roles And Responsibilities This role encompasses being the Sustainable Finance team senior analytical representative for APAC. Coordinate with the rating practices with regards to the roll out/delivery of Sustainable Finance products in APAC (ESG Evaluation, Green Evaluation); Senior Sustainable Finance expert in external engagements (Market outreach, sustomer interactions, ESG Evaluation preparedness meetings); Subject matter expert to support rating practices for ESG in ratings; Standing member of the ESG and Green Evaluation Steering Group; Contribute, as the Sustainable Finance expert for APAC, to individual ESG and Green Evaluations (either as primary evaluator or reviewer); Research and write thought leadership articles; Contribute to the development/enhancement of our ESG and Green Evaluation analytical approach; Be a champion of analytical and customer service excellence in the sustainable finance field in APAC as well as with regard to ESG in credit ratings; Contribute to seamless working environment across the Sustainable Finance group Success Will Be Measured By Quality of Green Evaluation and ESG evaluations produced in APAC (analytical excellence, quality of written reports, customer service); Capacity to establish an effective partnership with rating practices, to allow an orderly delivery of Sustainable Finance strategy; Contribution to ESG and Green Evaluation Steering group meetings as well as to thought leadership and market engagement; Compliance with relevant policies and procedures; Requirements At least seven years of relevant analytical experience, preferably in the field of Sustainable finance and within the APAC region, with some bias towards science-based qualification as well as finance/economics Strong communications skills and ability to represent the company at variety of high profile external conferences related to sustainable finance topics. A blend of strong leadership, analytical and organizational skills A good knowledge of S&P Global Ratings\u2019 methodologies and analytical approaches, especially related to Sustainable Finance Strong communicator with good interpersonal & soft skills Willingness to travel, sometimes at short notice About S&P Global Ratings S&P Global Ratings is the world\u2019s leading provider of independent credit ratings. Our ratings are essential to driving growth, providing transparency and helping educate market participants so they can make decisions with confidence. We have more than 1 million credit ratings outstanding on government, corporate, financial sector and structured finance entities and securities. We offer an independent view of the market built on a unique combination of broad perspective and local insight. We provide our opinions and research about relative credit risk; market participants gain independent information to help support the growth of transparent, liquid debt markets worldwide. S&P Global Ratings is a division of S&P Global (NYSE: SPGI), which provides essential intelligence for individuals, companies and governments to make decisions with confidence. For more information, visit www.spglobal.com/ratings S&P Global is an equal opportunity employer committed to making all employment decisions without regard to race/ethnicity, gender, pregnancy, gender identity or expression, color, creed, religion, national origin, age, disability, marital status (including domestic partnerships and civil unions), sexual orientation, military veteran status, unemployment status, or other legally protected categories, subject to applicable law. ", 
